png 1600w","height":1067}}}},"level":"block","ref":"686e6a44c2ac5393c741b0fb","type":"image"}],["p","While some may attribute Laopu’s rise to the soaring price of gold, a broader trend is more troubling for Western brands: Chinese consumers appear to be falling out of love with them. According to Morgan Stanley, the share of Chinese clients across Richemont brands declined steadily between March 2024 and March 2025 (down 15 per cent in March 2024, with a sharp dip of 20 per cent in September 2024, and down again in March 2025 by 8 per cent). Richemont offset these losses with growth in the US and Europe."],["inline-embed",{"props":{"dangerousCaption":"","dangerousCredit":"","image":{"id":"686e6a89d263477a717f8d3a","altText":"Image may contain Bow Weapon Chart and Line Chart","contentType":"photo","sources":{"sm":{"width":640,"url":"https:\u002F\u002Fassets.vogue.com\u002Fphotos\u002F686e6a89d263477a717f8d3a\u002Fmaster\u002Fw_640,c_limit\u002F0EWoS-richemont-group-growth-by-nationality.png","srcset":"https:\u002F\u002Fassets.vogue.com\u002Fphotos\u002F686e6a89d263477a717f8d3a\u002Fmaster\u002Fw_120,c_limit\u002F0EWoS-richemont-group-growth-by-nationality.png 120w, https:\u002F\u002Fassets.vogue.com\u002Fphotos\u002F686e6a89d263477a717f8d3a\u002Fmaster\u002Fw_240,c_limit\u002F0EWoS-richemont-group-growth-by-nationality.png 240w, https:\u002F\u002Fassets.vogue.com\u002Fphotos\u002F686e6a89d263477a717f8d3a\u002Fmaster\u002Fw_320,c_limit\u002F0EWoS-richemont-group-growth-by-nationality.png 320w, https:\u002F\u002Fassets.vogue.com\u002Fphotos\u002F686e6a89d263477a717f8d3a\u002Fmaster\u002Fw_640,c_limit\u002F0EWoS-richemont-group-growth-by-nationality.png 640w","height":427},"md":{"width":768,"url":"https:\u002F\u002Fassets.vogue.com\u002Fphotos\u002F686e6a89d263477a717f8d3a\u002Fmaster\u002Fw_768,c_limit\u002F0EWoS-richemont-group-growth-by-nationality.png","srcset":"https:\u002F\u002Fassets.vogue.com\u002Fphotos\u002F686e6a89d263477a717f8d3a\u002Fmaster\u002Fw_120,c_lim